93
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:56,030
This is a summary of what the
calculus of variations does.

94
00:05:56,030 --> 00:06:00,660
So it takes a
minimization problem.

95
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:03,840
So I'm looking for
a function u of x.

96
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:08,720
And always since we're
in continuous problems,

97
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:10,490
